<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1875" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hogna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hogna heeri" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Hogna heeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed by the genitalia: the males, according to literature, by a straight embolus (
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich, J" journalOrPublisher="Beitraege zur Araneologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 619" refId="B76" refString="Wunderlich, J, 1992. Die Spinnen-Fauna der Makaronesischen Inseln: Taxonomie, Oekologie, Biogeographie und Evolution. Beitraege zur Araneologie 1: 1 - 619" title="Die Spinnen-Fauna der Makaronesischen Inseln: Taxonomie, Oekologie, Biogeographie und Evolution." volume="1" year="1992">Wunderlich 1992</bibRefCitation>
: 595, fig. 720); in females, by epigynal anterior pockets with widely divergent lateral border and median septum with a wide posterior transverse part (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Hogna heeri female (CRBALC 0501): A epigyne, ventral B vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646989" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">9</figureCitation>
). Similar species include 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. insularum" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">H. insularum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. isambertoi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isambertoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">H. isambertoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., from which it cannot be somatically differentiated.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646989" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" start="Figure 9" startId="F9">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
